## 4. State Management Layout (`lib/blocs/`)

The application bootstraps multiple global Cubits inside `lib/main.dart` using a `MultiBlocProvider` wrap at the root `MyApp` level:

| Cubit Class Name | Directory Location | State / Target Responsibility |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `ThemeCubit` | `theme_bloc/` | Manages dark/light modes using key `ThemeModeType`. |
| `BluetoothPrinterCubit` | `bluetooth_printer_bloc/` | Handles receipt printer BLE connection & paper width options. |
| `LoadingCubit` | `loading_bloc/` | Toggles dynamic spinners/loading screens globally. |
| `UserDataCubit` | `userData_bloc/` | Persists session context for currently logged-in user. |
| `ItemCubit` | `item_bloc/` | Orchestrates structural stocks, categories, groups, types, and items. |
| `TransactionsCubit` | `transactions_bloc/` | Processes operations for checkout transactions, refunds, stock ins/outs. |
| `HistoryCubit` | `history_bloc/` | Exposes logs and chronological inventory audit tracks. |
| `PromotionCubit` | `promotion_bloc/` | Validates item-level and cart-wide discount parameters. |
| `ConfirmByPasswordCubit`| `confirm_by_password_bloc/` | Manages secure credentials confirmation for sensitive actions. |

### Cubit-to-Cubit Dependency Pattern:
When a Cubit requires dependencies from another, utilize Flutter BLoC's watch pattern within the `MultiBlocProvider` initialization block:
```dart
BlocProvider<ConfirmByPasswordCubit>(
  create: (ctx) {
    return ConfirmByPasswordCubit(userModel: ctx.watch<UserDataCubit>().state.userModel);
  },
  lazy: true,
)
```

